<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-10-10T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-10-10T09:00:00-05:00" n="774" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d774">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">760m.6111/31: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SLA1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-10-10T17:00:00+03:00">October
                                    10, 1939—5 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received October 10—1:36 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>721. My telegram 673, October 4, 2 p.m. Although no announcement thereof
                            has appeared in the Soviet press, I understand that in addition to the
                            meeting reported in my telegram under reference the Lithuanian
                            delegation had further conferences in the Kremlin on the following day.
                            The Commander-in-Chief of the Lithuanian Army<note n="47" xml:id="d774fn47">Gen. <persName corresp="#p_RS1">Stasys
                                    Rastikis</persName>.</note> and the Vice Premier left for Kaunas
                            yesterday morning and are expected back today. The Lithuanian Foreign
                            Minister and the other delegates have remained in Moscow. I have been
                            unable to ascertain <pb facs="1070" n="964" xml:id="pg_964"/> the
                            reasons for the delay in the conclusion of a Lithuanian-Soviet agreement
                            but I believe the delay has resulted from enlarged Soviet demands.</p>
                        <p>Repeated to the Legation at Kaunas.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_SLA1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>